      "activityCount": 1,
      "description": "This radiant golden hammer was forged in the temples of fortune and justice. Its surface shimmers with soft celestial light, and a lucky charm dangles from its hilt. The hammer blesses its wielder with divine strength—and occasional bursts of miraculous luck.\nWeapon Stats:\nType: Maul (2d6, heavy, two-handed) or Mace (1d6, one-handed)\nRarity: Very Rare\nRequires Attunement: Yes (Paladin or Cleric, good alignment)\nMagic Features:\n1. Divine Blessing\nYou gain a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this weapon.\n2. Fortune's Favor (1/long rest)\nWhen you miss an attack roll, fail an ability check, or fail a saving throw, you can choose to reroll the result. You must take the new roll.\n3. Radiant Smite (2/long rest)\nWhen you hit a creature with this weapon, you can choose to deal an extra 2d6 radiant damage. If the target is a fiend or undead, the radiant damage increases to 2d8.\n4. Glimmer of Luck (passive)\nWhile attuned, you gain a +1 bonus to initiative rolls and can’t be surprised while conscious.",
      "descriptionLength": 1016,
